{"title": "Man, 25, arrested for public nuisance on SIM campus", "tags": "singapore", "timestamp": "2024-08-08", "content": "SINGAPORE \u2013 A 25-year-old man was arrested on Aug 6 for public nuisance at the Singapore Institute of Management Global Education (SIM) campus in Clementi.\nThe police said they received a call for assistance at around 3.35pm that day at 461 Clementi Road, where SIM is located.\nIn a video of the arrest posted on Chinese social media platform Xiaohongshu on Aug 7, two police officers are shown holding on to the arms of a man wearing glasses.\nThe incident appears to be taking place during an event and a crowd is watching the officers make the arrest.\nThe man who was arrested can be heard shouting: \u201cYou cannot treat me like this! I was a student! I am a student... I\u2019m not leaving!\u201d\nHe is later seen with his hands behind his back while being escorted out of the building by three police officers.\nThe police said that investigations are ongoing.\nIn a media reply, an SIM spokesperson confirmed that the man was one of its students and that he is currently warded at the Institute of Mental Health for further evaluation."}